result.execSummary:
The defendant Luis Enrique Cruz Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 4th Degree Sexual Assault, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).
  • Sex with Child Age 16 or Older, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.09.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO APPLY.
* Provide a DNA sample (unless previously done) and PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO APPLY.
* No contact with children under the age of 17 years EXCEPT Court allows defendant to have contact with his biological children without restrictions.

* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* Cooperate and participate with a sex offender evaluation and follow any recommended treatment.

OTHER COURT ORDERS:
* Court ordered defendant to comply with the sex offender reporting requirement for a period of 10 years - STAYED until 09-12-2016.   Court will review this issue again on the upcoming Review Hearing date on 09-12-2016.

**MATTER HEARD BY JUDGE CONEN FOR JUDGE DONALD.....
Defendant Luis Enrique Cruz in court with attorney Eugene E. Detert.  Erin Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court addressed a housekeeping matter:  Court entered judgment of conviction as to Count #s 1 and 2.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION as straight time, consecutive to Count #2. 
Credit for 1  day time served. 

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION as straight time, consecutive to Count #1. 
Credit for ZERO days time served. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:  COURT STAYS sentences and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years under the supervision of Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* Cooperate and participate with a sex offender evaluation and follow any recommended treatment.
* As to Count 2 only:  SERVE 30 DAYS "condition time" at the House of Correction - STAYED to be used at the Court's discretion (Court may lift the stay of the condition time if defendant is non compliant with the sex offender treatment.)  Court will review this issue again on the upcoming Review Hearing date on 09-12-2016.
* No contact with children under the age of 17 years EXCEPT Court allows defendant to have contact with his biological children without restrictions.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO APPLY.
* Provide a DNA sample (unless previously done) and PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO APPLY.

OTHER COURT ORDERS:
* Court ordered defendant to comply with the sex offender reporting requirement for a period of 10 years - STAYED until 09-12-2016.   Court will review this issue again on the upcoming Review Hearing date on 09-12-2016.
 
Appeal rights given.

**MATTER HEARD BY JUDGE CONEN FOR JUDGE DONALD.....
Defendant Luis Enrique Cruz in court with attorney Eugene E. Detert.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder for Erin Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

**Note:  Plea taken today; needs factual basis.

Amended Information filed today.
Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of the Amended Information.
Defense counsel waived reading of the "Amended Information" and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court AMENDED Count #1 to:  Fourth Degree Sexual Assault [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 940.225(3m), 939.51(3)(a).  

Count #2 remains the same.

AS TO COUNT 1 (AMENDED TO A MISDEMEANOR):    Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

AS TO COUNT 2 (MISDEMEANOR):  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
